cxro.common.device.axis

Class HydraAxis

  • java.lang.Object
    • cxro.common.device.axis.AbstractAxis
      • cxro.common.device.axis.HydraAxis
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Axis

    public final class HydraAxis
extends AbstractAxis
    Device handler for MICOS Hydra axis controller. A Hydra axis is a stepper-driven stage, possibly closed-loop.

        NOTE: This will not assure that the motor is first stopped, nor that a brake will be applied. This must be performed separately by the application program before calling this method.

      • getSwitches

        public final boolean[] getSwitches()
                            throws java.io.IOException
        Description copied from interface: Axis
        This method returns an array of booleans that represent the current status of the hardware switches on the controller.

        They are in the form: {Reverse_Switch, Forward_Switch, Home_Switch}.
        When true, the switch is active.

        Ex:
           switches[] = xAxis.getRawSwitches();
           if(switches[1]) // test Forward_Switch
             //throw error or act accordingly.

        Specified by:
        getSwitches in interface Axis
        Specified by:
        getSwitches in class AbstractAxis
        Returns:
        switch array.

      • getStatus

        public final int getStatus()
                    throws java.io.IOException,
                           java.lang.InterruptedException
        Get RAW Axis Status.

        NOTE: This is unique to a HYDRA controller.

        This is a combination of flag bits

        • D15 : SYSTEM_ERROR, reset required
        • D14 : RESERVED
        • D13 : RESERVED
        • D12 : RESERVED
        • D11 : RESERVED
        • D10 : NOT_READY
        • D09 : EMERGENCY_SWITCH_ACTIVE
        • D08 : MOTOR_OFF
        • D07 : EMERGENCY_STOPPED
        • D06 : RESERVED
        • D05 : WITHIN TARGET WINDOW
        • D04 : RESERVED
        • D03 : RESERVED
        • D02 : MACHINE_ERROR
        • D01 : MANUAL_MODE
        • D00 : MOVING
        Returns:
        status word
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException
        java.lang.InterruptedException

      • getSystemError

        public final int getSystemError()
                         throws java.io.IOException
        Get Controller System Error.

        Error codeDescription
        1002Parameter stack underrun
        1003Parameter out of range
        1004Position range exceeded *
        1009Para stack lacking space (< 10 para. left)
        1010RS-232 input buffer lacking space (< 30 char. left)
        1015Limit setting inconsistent
        1100Limits switches states inconsistent / both active
        2000Unknown command

        If a move is terminated by either limit switch in spite of valid motion range limits, this will be indicated by code 1004. (This could, for instance, occur subsequent to loss of motor steps in open loop operation). If a manual alteration of the motion range by setnlimit would as a consequence invalidate the current axis coordinate, the controller will discard the setting, leave the limits unchanged and set code 1015. When a move is meant to target a position outside the currently valid motion range, the axis controller will target the respective position limit instead.

        Returns:
        error code (see Hydra Manual for details)
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException
